Complete OT/SCADA Module implementation for Forge platform:

Phase 1: OPC-UA client (asyncua wrapper, tag engine, path normalization, i3X discovery)
Phase 2: Scripting engine (ScriptEngine, ScriptSandbox, TriggerRegistry, RBAC, audit trail)
         + 5 core forge.* SDK modules (tag, db, net, log, alarm)
Phase 3: ISA-18.2 alarm engine (7-state machine, 9 alarm types, MQTT/RabbitMQ/CMMS integration)
         + embedded MQTT 3.1.1 broker
Phase 4: Control write interface (4-layer defense chain, interlock engine, write audit trail,
         MES recipe integration with batch tracking)
Phase 5: Ignition Bridge Adapter (REST API polling, tag path mapping, dual-write validation,
         health dashboard, operator acceptance checklist)
Phase 6: Script migration prep — 6 new forge.* SDK modules (date, dataset, perspective,
         file, util, security), API mapping reference for all 52 system.* calls,
         Tier 1 conversion targets identified (42 of 430 hand-written scripts)

FACTS spec v0.5.0: 21 data sources, 5 new script migration sources.
3275 tests passing, 0 regressions.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
